It's at a bit of a cusp:  how can Compaq justify selling a computer that 
IBM has deemed unworthy to sell to its customers?  Mind you, Compaq 
doesn't have its own chip waiting in the wings like IBM does with the 
PowerPC, but IBM still is perceived as the quality leader, so this latest 
announcement is a serious hit.  And, if it's enough to make Compaq follow 
suit, then it's curtains for the first-generation Pentiums.

This is one step closer to forcing a complete and total recall of all 
Pentia.  Don't think that doesn't pinch the sphyncter muscles of Intel 
execs just a wee bit.

